U.S. Violent Crime Declined 5.5% Last Year

-- B y   J e f f   B l i s s
-- 
2011-05-23T13:58:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/u-s-violent-crime-fell-5-5-percent-in-2010-fbi-reports-1-.html
Violent crime in the U.S. fell in
2010 for the fourth year in a row, the  Federal Bureau of
Investigation  said in a  preliminary  report.  Todayâ€™s report showed violent crime decreased 5.5 percent
compared with 2009, while property crime declined 2.8 percent.
All four of the violent crime categories -- forcible rape,
robbery, murder and non-negligent manslaughter, and aggravated
assault -- fell last year, the report said.  Murder and non-negligent manslaughter declined 4.4 percent,
rape was down 4.2 percent, robbery plunged 9.5 percent and
aggravated assault 3.6 percent, according to the  FBI .  All property crime categories -- larceny and theft,
burglary and motor-vehicle theft -- decreased, according to the
FBI.  The report is based on information provided by 13,007 law-
enforcement agencies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
